cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.CL, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper analyses social media data (Twitter) and examines the relationship between football and alcohol consumption during a major event.
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also a likely category as the paper explores the social and cultural aspects of alcohol consumption during a major sporting event.
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is a possible category as the paper may touch upon issues related to privacy and security of social media data.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possible category as the paper may use natural language processing techniques to analyse the Twitter data.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper may use information retrieval techniques to extract relevant information from the Twitter data.
